# EduFlow Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your values.

```env
# Clerk Authentication
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=/sign-up
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=/dashboard
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=/dashboard

# Convex
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.cloud
CONVEX_DEPLOY_KEY=prod:your-deploy-key

# Clerk JWT for Convex (from Clerk Dashboard → JWT Templates → Convex)
CLERK_JWT_ISSUER_DOMAIN=https://your-clerk-domain.clerk.accounts.dev

# Admin bootstrap (comma-separated emails auto-promoted to admin on first login)
ADMIN_EMAILS=admin@yourcompany.com

# App URL (production)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://your-domain.vercel.app
```

## Setup Order

1. Create Clerk application at https://clerk.com
2. Create Convex project at https://convex.dev
3. Configure Clerk JWT template named `convex`
4. Set `CLERK_JWT_ISSUER_DOMAIN` in Convex dashboard environment variables
5. Set `ADMIN_EMAILS` in Convex dashboard for admin bootstrap
6. Deploy Convex: `npx convex deploy`
7. Deploy Next.js to Vercel with env vars above
